The paper discusses a new architecture for training compact neural networks for visual recognition and text classification tasks, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically addresses the challenge of running machine learning models on devices with limited memory, which is a common concern in the field of mobile computing and embedded systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
